          "datePublished": "2019-04-07",
          "reviewRating": {
            "@type": "Rating",
            "ratingValue": "3",
            "bestRating": "5",
            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "It is an English medium co- educational residential school recognised by the State Government and affiliated to the Council for the Indian School Certificate Examinations, New Delhi and prepares children for the Indian Certificate of Secondary Education ( ICSE -10 ) and the Indian School Certificate ( ISC - 12 ) Examinations. These examinations are recognised by State Education Boards and Universities as equivalent to the High School and Intermediate examinations respectively, and after passing ISC - 12 examination, a child can either join graduate courses at any university or can compete for admission to professional courses such as medicine, engineering and technology and also for entrance to National Defence Academy, Khadakwasla (Pune) .\n\nThe school office, assembly flat, dining rooms, dormitories for girls and sub-junior boys are located in the main building, Pratap Bhawan, which has with it about 2 acres of land for playground and gardens. A spacious hall, with a seating capacity for 450, is situated close to Pratap Bhawan. The Auditorium also serves as an Assembly Hall, an indoor games complex, apart from other activities conducted here.\n\nThe class rooms are located in the academic block, another wing contiguous to the main building. Dormitories for senior boys, and science laboratories are located in Vivekanand Bhawan, adjacent to the academic block, on Camel's Back Road.\n\nProgrammes of S.U.P.W.(Socially Useful Productive Work) through 'Shrama-dan' are also organised.",
